<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,796,1469]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1119,1144]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Remarks.</emphasis>
Here, for the first time, we provide photographs of test surface details on this rarely seen temnopleurid (
<figureCitation box="[316,386,1156,1181]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1919,1941]" captionTargetBox="[179,1415,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[179,1415,193,1947]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 2. Test features of Microcyphus ceylanicus (WUSL/ER/87): A, aboral view; B, oral view; C, lateral view; D, ambital ambulacrum; E, ambital interambulacrum; F, oblique view through peristome showing an auricle D and E whitened with ammonium chloride." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2605944/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Its test has never been figured in detail, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen, T." box="[906,1120,1156,1180]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" refId="ref10563" refString="Mortensen, T. (1943 a) A Monograph of the Echinoidea III. 2. Camarodonta I. Orthopsidae, Glyphocyphidae, Temnopleuridae and Toxopneustidae. C. A. Reitzel, Copenhagen, 553 pp." type="book" year="1943">Mortensen (1943a)</bibRefCitation>
included only a photograph in lateral view, plus drawings of the apical system, ambulacral compounding, and some pedicellariae. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mortensen" authorityYear="1942" class="Echinoidea" family="Temnopleuridae" genus="Microcyphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="ceylanicus">
<emphasis box="[1405,1428,1193,1216]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,269,1228,1253]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">ceylanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to 
<collectingCountry box="[453,565,1228,1253]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
and the Andaman Islands, and can be distinguished from other Sri Lankan regular echinoids by its light olive-green test. The test has naked interambulacral areas, each of which has a dark zigzag line along the medial sutures (
<figureCitation box="[582,653,1300,1325]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1919,1941]" captionTargetBox="[179,1415,193,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[179,1415,193,1947]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 2. Test features of Microcyphus ceylanicus (WUSL/ER/87): A, aboral view; B, oral view; C, lateral view; D, ambital ambulacrum; E, ambital interambulacrum; F, oblique view through peristome showing an auricle D and E whitened with ammonium chloride." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2605944/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). The spines are banded with red, brown, and white. This species is characterized by its sharply delimited naked areas in both the interambulacra and ambulacra (
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen, T." box="[1196,1385,1336,1360]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" pagination="225 - 232" refId="ref10532" refString="Mortensen, T. (1942) New Echinoidea (Camarodonta). Preliminary notice. Videnskabelige Meddelelser fra Dansk naturhistorisk Forening i KObenhavn, 106, 225 - 232." type="journal article" year="1942">Mortensen 1942</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,796,1469]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">
<bibRefCitation author="Doderlein, L." box="[199,392,1372,1397]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" pagination="821 - 846" refId="ref9470" refString="Doderlein, L. (1888) Echinodermen von Ceylon. Bericht uber die von den Herren D res Sarasin gesammelten Asteroidea, Ophiuroidea und Echinoidea. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Abteilung fur Systematik, Geographie und Biologie der Tiere, 3, 821 - 846. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 1933" type="journal article" year="1888">Döderlein (1888)</bibRefCitation>
misidentified this species as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. Agassiz in L. Agassiz &amp; Desor" authorityYear="1846" box="[719,872,1372,1397]" class="Echinoidea" family="Temnopleuridae" genus="Microcyphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Camarodonta" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="maculatus">
<emphasis box="[719,872,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">M. maculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an error that was rectified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen, T." box="[1215,1432,1372,1396]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42" refId="ref10563" refString="Mortensen, T. (1943 a) A Monograph of the Echinoidea III. 2. Camarodonta I. Orthopsidae, Glyphocyphidae, Temnopleuridae and Toxopneustidae. C. A. Reitzel, Copenhagen, 553 pp." type="book" year="1943">Mortensen (1943a)</bibRefCitation>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[207,255,1408,1432]" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
specimen, collected from 
<collectingCountry box="[576,695,1407,1432]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="7" pageNumber="42">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
, is housed at the Zoologische Staatssammlung München (The Bavarian State Collection of Zoology, Munich).
</paragraph>
